abstract: MINEOLA  THE first hint of the Long Island Lighting Company's $228 million proposed rate increase was the loose leaf notebooks. Unlike Lilco's annual report, which  had contained 38 pages and a full-color sketch of the Shoreham nuclear generating plant, these four notebooks weighed 15 pounds and contained at least 500 pages.
